  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: Policy H9 of Islington's Unitary Development Plan states that the conversion of smaller properties of less than 120 square metres gross floor area will not normally be permitted. The supporting text to the policy makes it clear that the Council will seek to retain houses which are best suited to single family occupation. It points out that two bedroom units do not properly satisfy the continuing demand for family accommodation, stating that units with small floor areas do not generally convert in a way that at least one good-sized unit can be provided. The proposal conflicts with the provisions of Policy H8 & the applicant has failed to demonstrate that any exceptional circumstances exist which would justify a departure from the requirements of that policy."
